<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<!--@import "_head.kit"-->

<body>
    <!--@import "_header.kit"-->

    <main>
        <article class="project-detail">
            <header class="project-detail-hero section-fade">
                <div class="container narrow">
                    <a href="/portfolio.html" class="back-link">Back to portfolio</a>
                    <p class="eyebrow">Project Three</p>
                    <h1>Wise Quests: Turning Financial Freedom into a Guided Learning Journey</h1>
                    <p class="lead">A product concept for Wise Young Explorer that helps parents give teenagers more
                        financial autonomy through visibility, challenges and goal-based saving — balancing parental
                        reassurance with teen motivation.</p>
                </div>
            </header>

            <section class="project-media-section">
                <div class="container">
                    <div class="project-cover project-cover-three project-cover-wide"></div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="project-body-section">
                <div class="container detail-grid">
                    <div class="detail-content">
                        <h2>Overview</h2>
                        <p>Wise Young Explorer helps teenagers save, spend and receive money across currencies while
                            parents retain oversight and control. The challenge was to design an experience that feels
                            reassuring for parents but still simple, useful and motivating for teens.</p>

                        <p> The key tension was clear: parents want safety and responsibility, while teenagers want
                            freedom and independence. The solution needed to work for both audiences without directly
                            marketing to minors or creating a separate brand.</p>
                        <h2>Process</h2>
                        <p>My contribution focused on research, interviews, insight synthesis, ideation, wireframes and
                            case narrative. Together with the team, we structured the solution around three pillars:
                            Visibility, Challenges and Goals.</p>

                        <p>Visibility gives teens access to basic money awareness through balance, notifications and
                            spending tracking. Challenges turn everyday responsibilities into rewarded actions. Goals
                            help teens connect short-term financial behavior with future aspirations.</p>
                    </div>
                    <aside class="project-facts">
                        <h2>Details</h2>
                         <dl>
                            <dt>Date</dt>
                            <dd>March 2026</dd>
                            <dt>Team</dt>
                            <dd>3 members</dd>
                            <dt>Context</dt>
                            <dd>Academic / New Blood Awards 2026</dd>
                            <dt>Role</dt>
                            <dd>Research / Insight Synthesis / Ideation / Wireframes / Storytelling</dd>
                            <dt>Methods:</dt>
                            <dd>Benchmarking, Interviews, Problem Framing, Low-Fidelity Wireframes, Product Narrative</dd>
                            <dt>Core pillars:</dt>
                            <dd>Visibility, Challenges, Goals</dd>
                        </dl>
                    </aside>
                </div>
            </section>
        </article>
    </main>

    <!--@import "_footer.kit"-->
